        "content": "<p>For debugging, it would have been helpful to me to have this delaborator:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/-- Delaborator for `no_index`. -/</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">delab</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mdata</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">delabNoIndex</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Delab</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">do</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mdata</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">SubExpr</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">getExpr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failure</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">some</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ofBool</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">find</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`noindex</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">failure</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">erase</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`noindex</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">withReader</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">subExpr</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">expr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mdata</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"o\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">delab</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">no_index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Having this enabled by default would certainly be confusing; Is the appropriate thing to do here to hide this behind a new <code>pp</code> option, or make the delaborator attribute scoped?</p>",
